infos.info: Broadcast history: - Originally broadcast from WXYZ in Detroit, first on Fridays, then Tuesdays and Thursdays. - April 12,1938, began its run on Mutual, in various time slots. - On Nov. 16, 1939, went to Blue Network/ABC in various time slots between 4:30 and 8:30 pm, on various days, sometimes twice a week. Also heard on some Mutual stations in 1940-41. - On the air with few gaps from Nov. 16, 1939,- Sept. 8, 1950, returned Sept. 10-Dec. , 1952. Mostly sustaining but also sponsored by General Mills Jan.-Aug.1948.Sponsored by Orange Crush Sept.-Dec. 1952. (This information from Dunning's Encyclopedia). - A very detailed broadcast history is contained in Hickerson's book. - -------------------------------------------------- - Genre: juvenile crime drama
